      "writtenOn": "2026-05-27T04:12:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sharing some context: these three interfaces (UUID, Power.Cap, SKU) are published by dbus-sensors on the chassis Board path, while the path itself is owned by Entity-Manager — so two services share the same D-Bus path with disjoint interface sets. The main chassis-discovery getSubTree keys on Item.Board / Item.Chassis, which only resolves to Entity-Manager on this path, so the three interfaces above cannot be picked up in the same pass and a second mapper hop scoped to the discovered path is needed. I agree this shape is not the cleanest. If you have a preferred pattern in mind for handling chassis paths shared by multiple owners, I would really appreciate your guidance and am happy to refactor\naccordingly. Thank you for the careful review.\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/90469",
